boolean

data type

- defined in [stdbool.h] (since C99)
- no printf-specifier for bools; use e.g. %d
- false == 0, true == 1
    - 0 represents logical false
    - any value different from 0 represents logical true

- SEE ALSO
    - primer, ch.3
    - modern, ch.3

EXAMPLE
#include <stdbool.h>

bool x = true;
printf(!x ? "true" : "false"); // false
